main event: An observer reported seeing two unidentified objects in the sky on 28 August 1966 in Oregon, Wisconsin.
interesting points: The first object was described as a bright orange object that appeared stationary before changing position,The second object looked elongated and was sighted later,The first object was initially thought to have a propeller,The observer estimated the distance of the object to be between 1/2 to 2 miles away,The sighting lasted for approximately 5 minutes with no photographs taken.
